comments.body: @kelea99 I'm still confused - aren't those just about pages? Like can't you add one the same way virtual gallery tour was added?

You can add them vertically (via dropdown). You cannot add another navigation item horizontally. 
So you have up-to and not exceeding 4 static tabs that can be activated horizontally in the navigation bar:
1. home
2. Curated Features (with dropdowns of subpages)
3. Browse
4. About (when you click on about, you will be directed to a page and sidebar with the other subpages)

Thanks @sandbergja , that's a good point. I can see two ways of addressing that:

1. Add a migration that adds unspecified "Accessible: true" to some value in the new `accessibility_needs` field - e.g. `['Unspecified accessibility need]` or something like that
2. Display both the old Accessible boolean and the new accessibility_needs array on the show view

Thanks, @maxkadel !

>     1. Add a migration that adds unspecified "Accessible: true" to some value in the new `accessibility_needs` field - e.g. `['Unspecified accessibility need]` or something like that

I like option 1 better — it seems like a less complex ui, and would make it easier if we wanted to remove the boolean field eventually.

pulfalight.title: Implement new access note data model

comments.body:
1) OPEN. Collection-level, series-level or component-level access type is blank or has type "open": this is considered equal to "open" and no badge should display. 
2) REVIEW. Collection-level, or series-level access type is "review": display badge "Restrictions may apply. See Access note." (yellow) (not used at component level)
3) RESTRICTED. Collection-level, series-level, or component-level access type is "restricted": display badge "Restricted content." (red)

Restriction types filter DOWN from collection level and file group level. No need for restriction types to filter up from components any longer.

researchdata.title: Events and Workshops are not displaying on homepage and Training and Events page

comments.body: The issue appears to that all the entries that are blank do not have a "Location" field value. The Drupal views that display the list in both places require that field, because the html template that builds the display for the linkable entry in the list is stored in the "rewrite results" configuration option for that field in the view.

We are actually imported libcal RSS for this site. Configuration is here: https://github.com/pulibrary/researchdata/blob/9cb10e956bcb603e3f733fa33c40f10b69e70a00/sites/default/config/migrate_plus.migration.event_rss_importer.yml#L50

It appears we need the libcal:location element to be populated.
The project is no longer utilizing ServiceNow at this time.  Closing.
